component "nodus.lock\ntyped default target" as GraphDecl #BBDEFB
component "@Entity\noptional sync mode or target override" as EntityDecl #BBDEFB
component "Generated typed target enum + registry\nentity descriptor groups + capability validation" as TargetRegistry #C8E6C9
component "One physical durable scheduler\nfair work-kind/target/direction lanes" as Scheduler #E1BEE7

GraphDecl --> TargetRegistry : infer default routing
EntityDecl --> TargetRegistry : inherit default; override only intent
TargetRegistry --> Scheduler

package "MODE IS AN AUTHORITY CONTRACT" as Modes #E8F5E9 {
  component "localOnly\nDrift only\nlocal mutations: yes\nqueue / pull: none" as LocalOnly #C8E6C9
  component "replicated\nlocal mutations: yes\naccepted remote base + pending overlay\npush + ordered pull + conflict rebase" as Replicated #C8E6C9
  component "imported\nremote authoritative\nordinary local mutation API: absent\nordered pull only" as Imported #C8E6C9
  component "exported\nDrift authoritative\nlocal mutations + idempotent outbox\nreceipt; no remote base/rebase" as Exported #C8E6C9
}

TargetRegistry --> LocalOnly : no target → safe default
TargetRegistry --> Replicated : graph default or entity target
TargetRegistry --> Imported : explicit only
TargetRegistry --> Exported : explicit only

package "SYNC TARGET ADAPTERS\ntransport is replaceable; domain is unchanged" as Targets #FFF3E0 {
  component "SupabaseSyncAdapter\nSQL schema + RLS + RPC + log" as Supabase #FFE0B2
  component "ConvexSyncAdapter\nnon-SQL protocol/provisioning" as Convex #FFE0B2
  component "NamedExternalApiSyncAdapter\nonly if it satisfies declared mode capabilities" as External #FFE0B2
  component "MultiMasterProtocolAdapter\none deterministic merge/recovery authority contract" as MultiMaster #FFE0B2
}

Scheduler --> Supabase : generated target lane
Scheduler --> Convex : generated target lane
Scheduler --> External : generated target lane
Scheduler --> MultiMaster : one encapsulated authority lane
Replicated ..> Scheduler
Imported ..> Scheduler
Exported ..> Scheduler

note right of Targets
  An entity names a stable target identifier, never an adapter class.
  The composition root supplies exactly one compatible adapter per used target.
  There is no handwritten entity-to-adapter map.
end note

package "SECONDARY PROJECTIONS — NEVER AUTHORITIES" as ProjectionPackage #E8F5E9 {
  component "Generated typed projection outbox\ninferred codec · routing · operation ID\nexplicit mapper only for changed semantics" as Projections #C8E6C9
  component "Search · analytics · calendar\nnotification · webhook · materialized view" as ProjectionTargets #C8E6C9
  Projections --> ProjectionTargets : independent idempotent receipts
}

Scheduler --> Projections : independent failure-isolated lanes

package "ORDERED CAPABILITY — SEMANTICS, NOT sortOrder" as Order #F3E5F5 {
  component "implements Ordered" as Ordered #E1BEE7
  component "Infer canonical typed scope tuple\nrelationship source → hierarchy → owner → bounded root\nexplicit orderScope only resolves ambiguity" as Scope #E1BEE7
  component "Generated collection operations\nappend · prepend · moveBefore · moveAfter\nrelationship moveFirst · moveLast · neighbor moves\nexact operations only with a boundedness proof\nexact scope parameters → atomic transfer" as OrderApi #E1BEE7
  component "Internal scalable rank\nindex = stored scope + lifecycle + rank + stable ID" as Rank #E1BEE7
  component "Remote canonical scope lane\nhierarchy partition + deterministic source/target locks\nmonotonic typed {scope, version} receipts" as CanonicalOrder #E1BEE7

  Ordered --> Scope
  Scope --> OrderApi
  OrderApi --> Rank
  Rank --> CanonicalOrder
}

Replicated --> CanonicalOrder : semantic operation carries scope base version

note bottom of Order
  Creation/removal/restoration/move/reorder/transfer share the same scope lock and version.
  Local and remote transfers reserve source + target lanes in deterministic key order.
  Recursive transfer adds an owner/hierarchy-partition lock for cycle safety.
  Transfer returns source + target receipts and appends by default.
  Scope fields are immutable to ordinary edits. A move normally writes one member;
  unbounded recovery expands keyset-indexed windows geometrically and never loads the scope.
  Transaction-local optimistic members participate in the next boundary calculation.
end note

note bottom of Scheduler
  One entity has one authority contract and may have several non-authoritative projections.
  Projection failure never rolls authoritative state back.
  Cross-target foreign keys, collaboration joins, or remote atomic invariants are rejected
  unless an explicit loose-reference, saga, or integration-event contract owns compensation.
end note
@enduml


